.TH "devm_gen_pool_create" 9 "devm_gen_pool_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_gen_pool_create \- managed gen_pool_create
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct gen_pool *" devm_gen_pool_create
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "int min_alloc_order "  ","
.BI "int nid "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device that provides the gen_pool
.IP "min_alloc_order" 12
log base 2 of number of bytes each bitmap bit represents
.IP "nid" 12
node selector for allocated gen_pool, NUMA_NO_NODE for all nodes
.IP "name" 12
name of a gen_pool or NULL, identifies a particular gen_pool on device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Create a new special memory pool that can be used to manage special purpose
memory not managed by the regular kmalloc/kfree interface. The pool will be
automatically destroyed by the device management code.
